 {
  "text": "First, on a tight budget, she decided to shop around before buying anything. Then she browsed the stalls, which were far cheaper than the tourist shops. She spotted a knock-off bag that was badly overpriced and walked away. At the next stall she haggled and talked the seller down by ten euros. Finally, she bought a jacket that was such good value for money it felt like a steal.",
